CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 8, 1960, pg. 16, reads: "No Worries - Don Hoak, left, and Gene Baker, veteran Pittsburgh Pirate infielders, didn't appear to be bothered in the least by 'Yankee pressure' before the beginning of the first World Series game at Forbes Field on Wednesday. The Bucs didn't either, as they won the opener, 6-4. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh Pirates baseball players Don Hoak and Gene Baker standing on field before opening game of 1960 World Series, Forbes Field
